author: HelloFresh
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sweet-as-honey-dijon-chicken-618be4f6e8b61739d04ab72f
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce (except cauliflower rice).

Trim @Green Beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Peel and mince or grate @Garlic{1%clove}. Zest and quarter @Lemon{1}.

Place @Riced Cauliflower{6%ounce} in a medium #microwave-safe bowl{} with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Cover bowl with #plastic wrap{} and poke a few holes in wrap. Microwave until tender, about ~{5%minutes}. Carefully uncover (watch out for steam!) and set aside.

Meanwhile, toss green beans on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @oil, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Transfer to a #cutting board{}; tent with #foil{} to keep warm.

Return pan used for chicken over medium-high heat. Add @water{1/4%cup} and half the @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1}. Cook, scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pan, until thickened slightly, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat. Stir in @Honey Dijon Dressing{1.5%ounce} and @Butter{1%tablespoon}. Season with salt and pepper.

While sauce cooks, heat a drizzle of oil in a medium pan over medium-high heat. Add cauliflower rice and garlic; cook until garlic is fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add remaining @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1} and @water{1/4%cup}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until water has mostly absorbed and cauliflower is tender, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon}, @Monterey Jack Cheese{1/4%cup}, and @Butter{1%tablespoon} until melted. Remove from heat.

> If mixture seems too thick, stir in a splash of water.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Toss green beans with a squeeze of lemon juice and lemon zest to taste.

Divide chicken, green beans and cauliflower rice between plates. Drizzle sauce over chicken and serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.